It is caused by the brain’s natural process of shutting down certain functions while sleeping. During this period, the person may feel as though they are unable to move or speak, even though they are still asleep. Sleep paralysis can be accompanied by hallucinations, such as seeing or hearing things that aren’t there. In some cases, people with sleep paralysis have reported experiencing lucid dreams, which are dreams in which the person is aware that they are dreaming. SVMs work by finding the maximum margin hyperplane in the feature space to separate different classes. The hyperplane is defined by a set of support vectors that lie on the boundary between two classes.
